e and Technology Meijo University"}, "affiliation-id": {"@afid": "60027762"}}, "author": [{"ce:given-name": "Minoru", "preferred-name": {"ce:given-name": "Minoru", "ce:initials": "M.", "ce:surname": "Fukaya", "ce:indexed-name": "Fukaya M."}, "@seq": "3", "ce:initials": "M.", "@_fa": "true", "@type": "auth", "ce:surname": "Fukaya", "@auid": "57190346842", "ce:indexed-name": "Fukaya M."}]}, {"affiliation": {"country": "India", "postal-code": "110012", "@afid": "60114515", "@country": "ind", "city": "New Delhi", "organization": [{"$": "National Research Center on Plant Biotechnology"}, {"$": "IARI"}], "affiliation-id": [{"@afid": "60114515"}, {"@afid": "60014344"}]}, "author": [{"ce:given-name": "Vandna", "preferred-name": {"ce:given-name": "Vandna", "ce:initials": "V.", "ce:surname": "Rai", "ce:indexed-name": "Rai V."}, "@seq": "4", "ce:initials": "V.", "@_fa": "true", "@type": "auth", "ce:surname": "Rai", "@auid": "7006076406", "ce:indexed-name": "Rai V."}]}], "citation-title": "Nitrate and amino acid availability affects glycine betaine and mycosporine-2-glycine in response to changes of salinity in a halotolerant cyanobacterium Aphanothece halophytica", "abstracts": "\u00a9 FEMS 2015. All rights reserved.A halotolerant cyanobacterium Aphanothece halophytica thrives in extreme salinity with accumulation of a potent osmoprotectant glycine betaine. Recently, this cyanobacterium was shown to accumulate sunscreen molecule mycosporine-2-glycine significantly at high salinity. In this study, we investigated effects of nitrate and amino acid provision on the accumulation of glycine betaine and mycosporine-2-glycine. With elevated nitrate concentrations at high salinity, intracellular levels of both metabolites were enhanced. Six-fold high nitrate concentration increased the relative amounts of glycine betaine and mycosporine-2-glycine to be 1.5 and 2.0 folds compared with control condition. Increased levels were time- and dose-dependent manner. Exogenous supply of glycine/serine at high salinity resulted in the similar trends as observed in excess nitrate experiment. Intracellular level of glycine betaine increased ~1.6 folds with glycine/serine supplementation. These supplementations also caused the increased level of mycosporine-2-glycine, namely 1.4 and 2 folds by glycine and serine, respectively. The transcription of glycine betaine and mycosporine-2-glycine biosynthetic genes was strongly induced under high-nitrate-salt condition. These results suggest the dependence of glycine betaine and mycosporine-2-glycine productions on substrate availability, and the effect of nitrate was possibly associated with stimulation of osmoprotectant increment in this extremophile.", "correspondence": {"affiliation": {"country": "Japan", "address-part": "1-501 Shiogamaguchi, Tenpaku-ku", "postal-code": "468-8502", "@country": "jpn", "city": "Nagoya", "organization": {"$": "Research Institute of Meijo University"}}, "person": {"ce:given-name": "Teruhiro", "ce:initials": "T.", "ce:surname": "Takabe", "ce:indexed-name": "Takabe T."}}, "citation-info": {"author-keywords": {"author-keyword": [{"$": "Amino acids", "@xml:lang": "eng"}, {"$": "Glycine betaine", "@xml:lang": "eng"}, {"$": "Halotolerant cyanobacterium", "@xml:lang": "eng"}, {"$": "Mycosporine-2-glycine", "@xml:lang": "eng"}, {"$": "Nitrate", "@xml:lang": "eng"}, {"$": "salt stress", "@xml:lang": "eng"}]}, "citation-type": {"@code": "ar"}, "citation-language": {"@language": "English", "@xml:lang": "eng"}, "abstract-language": {"@language": "English", "@xml:lang": "eng"}}, "source": {"website": {"ce:e-address": {"$": "http://femsle.oxfordjournals.org/", "@type": "email"}}, "translated-sourcetitle": {"$": "FEMS Microbiology Letters", "@xml:lang": "eng"}, "volisspag": {"voliss": {"@volume": "362", "@issue": "23"}}, "@type": "j", "sourcetitle": "FEMS Microbiology Letters", "publicationdate": {"month": "12", "year": "2015", "date-text": "December 2015", "day": "01"}, "codencode": "FMLED", "sourc