e/serine supplementation. These supplementations also caused the increased level of mycosporine-2-glycine, namely 1.4 and 2 folds by glycine and serine, respectively. The transcription of glycine betaine and mycosporine-2-glycine biosynthetic genes was strongly induced under high-nitrate-salt condition. These results suggest the dependence of glycine betaine and mycosporine-2-glycine productions on substrate availability, and the effect of nitrate was possibly associated with stimulation of osmoprotectant increment in this extremophile.", "pubmed-id": "26474598", "prism:coverDate": "2015-12-01", "prism:aggregationType": "Journal", "prism:url": "https://api.elsevier.com/content/abstract/scopus_id/84982133085", "dc:creator": {"author": [{"ce:given-name": "Rungaroon", "preferred-name": {"ce:given-name": "Rungaroon", "ce:initials": "R.", "ce:surname": "Waditee-Sirisattha", "ce:indexed-name": "Waditee-Sirisattha R."}, "@seq": "1", "ce:initials": "R.", "@_fa": "true", "affiliation": [{"@id": "60027762", "@href": "https://api.elsevier.com/content/affiliation/affiliation_id/60027762"}, {"@id": "60028190", "@href": "https://api.elsevier.com/content/affiliation/affiliation_id/60028190"}], "ce:surname": "Waditee-Sirisattha", "@auid": "6603105684", "author-url": "https://api.elsevier.com/content/author/author_id/6603105684", "ce:indexed-name": "Waditee-Sirisattha R."}]}, "link": [{"@_fa": "true", "@rel": "self", "@href": "https://api.elsevier.com/content/abstract/scopus_id/84982133085"}, {"@_fa": "true", "@rel": "scopus", "@href": "https://www.scopus.com/inward/record.uri?partnerID=HzOxMe3b&scp=84982133085&origin=inward"}, {"@_fa": "true", "@rel": "scopus-citedby", "@href": "https://www.scopus.com/inward/citedby.uri?partnerID=HzOxMe3b&scp=84982133085&origin=inward"}], "source-id": "19706", "citedby-count": "32", "prism:volume": "362", "subtype": "ar", "dc:title": "Nitrate and amino acid availability affects glycine betaine and mycosporine-2-glycine in response to changes of sal